      the definition of <tex>S</tex>. To show <tex>j( \bigwedge  S)  \le  j(x)</tex>, it suffices
      to show <tex>\bigwedge  S  \le  x</tex> which holds by definition.
    </li>    <li>      Let <tex>x  \in  L</tex>, <tex>y  \in   \mathfrak{F} _j</tex>. We need to show that
